<p>Upgrading was a breeze:</p>
<ol>
<li>I dumped the old database tables and copied them over here.</li>
<li>I installed this site with the usual defaults included near-empty tables.</li>
<li>Then I fed my old db tables back in, changed the prefix in wp_config.php to point at those old tables.</li>
<li>I changed the siteurl and home in the options table to point at the new url.</li>
<li>Finally, I visited the upgrade url which magically brought the db up to date!</li>
</ol>
<p>I decided on using <a href="http://getk2.com/">K2</a>, and modified the default theme slightly to match my old theme somewhat. Unfortunately I had to edit index.php so I have to watch out when I'm upgrading.</p>
